        "source": [
          "# Model-B: Conditional GAN Data Augmentation for Skin Cancer Classification\n",
          "### IT504 Project — HAM10000 (Skin Cancer)\n",
          "**Student:** Abdulrahman Alqarni\n",
          "\n",
          "This notebook runs the **complete experiment** end-to-end:\n",
          "\n",
          "1. Download & preprocess the HAM10000 dataset\n",
          "2. Hold out a fixed test set (used by BOTH models — never augmented)\n",
          "3. **Model-A (baseline):** train SVM, Decision Tree, Random Forest, Naive Bayes on the *original* training data\n",
          "4. Train a **Conditional GAN (cGAN)** and generate synthetic images for the minority classes\n",
          "5. **Model-B (augmented):** train the SAME four models on the *augmented* training data\n",
          "6. Compare A vs B — metrics, bar charts, ROC curves, confusion matrices, and minority-class improvement\n",
          "\n",
          "> **Important for a fair comparison:** preprocessing, train/test split, and model settings are IDENTICAL for A and B. The ONLY difference is that Model-B's *training* set also contains GAN-generated images. The test set is never touched by the GAN.\n",
          "\n",
          "**Runtime:** Set Colab to GPU — `Runtime → Change runtime type → T4 GPU`.\n"
        ]
      },
